# Security headers for Mindline (Cloudflare). The CSP is strict by design:
# the room key lives in the URL fragment, so no third-party script may ever
# run (PROTOCOL.md §6). Fonts are self-hosted; there is no WASM.

# CSP is emitted by SvelteKit (svelte.config.js kit.csp) with hashed
# inline scripts; defining it here too would intersect and break.

# Cache-Control: no-store on /* is load-bearing. A zone-level cache rule
# once cached the HTML at the edge; after a deploy the stale HTML pointed
# at hashed chunks that no longer existed and the app went down entirely
# (2026-06-11). Documents and unhashed files must never be edge-cached.
# Hashed build assets are re-allowed below and by the adapter-appended
# rules (a later rule wins for the same header).
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  X-DNS-Prefetch-Control: off
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(self), microphone=(self), geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Cache-Control: no-store

# Immutable build assets only
/_app/immutable/*
  ! Cache-Control
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
